Use the following CMake targets to import palloc:

  find_package(palloc CONFIG REQUIRED)
  target_link_libraries(main PRIVATE palloc)

And use palloc in your sources as:

  #include <palloc.h>
  #include <stdio.h>
  int main(int argc, char** argv) {
    int* p = palloc_malloc_tp(int);
    *p = palloc_version();
    printf("palloc version: %d\n", *p);
    palloc_free(p);
    return 0;
  }

When dynamically overriding on Windows, ensure `palloc.dll` is linked through some call to
palloc (e.g. `palloc_version()`), and that the `palloc-redirect.dll` is in the same directory.
See https://github.com/microsoft/palloc/blob/dev/bin/readme.md for detailed information.
